Runs a WMI query and formats the results.

Inputs\:
wqlQuery - the query to run.
namespace - the wmi namespace to run the query in.
host - the host to run the query against.
user - a user to authenticate with host as.
password - the password for user.
format - How to format the query's results (text or csv).

Responses\:
success - the operation succeeded.
failure - an error occurred.
9c82c923-ebee-41b6-a730-8fafac5ddf77.46a9e3f4-f647-4904-b3dc-c60bb6a6ef3b.transition.description=${host} should have ${expectedVirtual} kb of virtual memory. 9c82c923-ebee-41b6-a730-8fafac5ddf77.4b19cad0-3e21-4b71-a202-87acae5bf1eb.description=
Retrieves the requested Windows Performance Counter Value.  Takes 5 samples back to back and returns the average.

Input Parameters\:
host - hostname or ip address of the target machine
object - the counter object (ex. Processor)
counter - the counter's name (ex. % Processor Time)
instance - the instance of the counter (if applicable) (ex. _Total)
user - username to connect as
password - password for user

Responses\:
PASSED - retrieved the counter successfully
FAILED - failed to retrieve the counter

Extra Results\:
VALUE - the actual value captured

Notes\:
This operation checks the value of a performance counter that must be running on the target windows host prior to flow execution\:
Performance Object\: memory
Performance Counter\: pages/sec
This performance counter can be enabled using PerfMon.exe on the target host.

Checks for any memory errors.

inputs\:
diagnostic so far - used to chain diagnostics together, and get one report. The output of previous diagnostics, or blank.
freeMemoryThreshold - % of total memory that should not be in use as a decimal.
freePagingThreshold - Number of kilobytes of paging file expected to not be in use.
maxPagesPerSecond - Maximum \# of memory pages per second considered acceptable.
minimumTotalMemory - A minimum value of memory that this computer is expected to have.
host - host to check.
user - username to login to host with.
password - password for user.

Responses\:
success - Diagnostic successful.
failure - something went wrong.

Notes\:
This flow checks the value of a performance counter that must be running on the target windows host prior to flow execution\:
Performance Object\: memory
Performance Counter\: pages/sec
This performance counter can be enabled using PerfMon.exe on the target host.

staticBinding.value:
The simplest resolution is to add additional memory to ${host}
the other resolutions may also help in some cases:
1) If memory cannot be added, get faster drives and/or split your paging files across multiple disks. While this will not decrease the number of pages per second, and can decrease the effect of these being high.
2) Shut down unneccesary services.
